  <refentry id="function.monetdb-connect">
   <refnamediv>
    <refname>monetdb_connect</refname>
    <refpurpose>Open a connection to a MonetDB Server</refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
   <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>
     <methodsynopsis>
      <type>resource</type><methodname>monetdb_connect</methodname>
      <methodparam choice="opt"><type>string</type><parameter>language</parameter></methodparam>
      <methodparam choice="opt"><type>string</type><parameter>hostname</parameter></methodparam>
      <methodparam choice="opt"><type>string</type><parameter>port</parameter></methodparam>
      <methodparam choice="opt"><type>string</type><parameter>username</parameter></methodparam>
      <methodparam choice="opt"><type>string</type><parameter>password</parameter></methodparam>
     </methodsynopsis>
    <para>
     Returns a MonetDB link identifier on success, or &false; on failure.
    </para>
    <para>
     <function>monetdb_connect</function> establishes a connection
     to a MonetDB server. 
	 The default parameter values are described in 
	 <link linkend="monetdb.configuration">MonetDB configuration options</link>
    </para>
    <para>
	 Please remember, that (unlike most other DBMSes) <literal>MonetDB</literal>
	 supports a rich and extendable set of languages.
	 That means, you should make sure the language you want to use is supported
	 by the server you're connecting to.
    </para>
	<para>
	 After successfull connection to MonetDB server, the established
	 link becomes a default parameter for all MonetDB functions, until another
	 connection is open or <function>monetdb_close</function> is called.
	</para>
	
    <para>
     <example>
      <title><function>monetdb_connect</function> example</title>
      <programlisting role="php">
<![CDATA[
<?php
$link = monetdb_connect();
if (!$link) {
    die('Could not connect: ' . monetdb_error());
}
echo 'Connected successfully';
monetdb_close();
?>
]]>
      </programlisting>
     </example>
    </para>
    <para> 
     See also
     <function>monetdb_close</function> and
	 <function>monetdb_query</function>
    </para>
   </refsect1>
  </refentry>

